 and letting students know that when they make some changes they have to review their code for possible breakage.  Well, most didn't, they just continued on and when the code was tested it broke.  Same type of logic applies to classes in EQ.  You stretch things too far for some classes and nerf others you'd better be willing to review what you did and adjust or you will possibly have broken something.</P><P> </font></td>
